 | id={{MR|449695}}.{{jstor|3689565}}|
}} </ref> The problem had been raised by [[Claude Lemar<U+00E9>chal|Lemar<U+00E9>chal]]'s reporting of solving ''non<U+2013>convex'' problems to within three&nbsp;percent of optimality.<ref> Page 38: {{citation|last=Lemar<U+00E9>chal|first=Claude|authorlink=Claude Lemar<U+00E9>chal|title=Utilisation de la dualit<U+00E9> dans les probl<U+00E9>mes non&nbsp;convexes [Use of duality for non<U+2013>convex problems]|year=1973|month=''Avril''&nbsp;[April]|number=16|location=Domaine de&nbsp;Voluceau, [[Rocquencourt]],&nbsp;78150 [[Le Chesnay|Le&nbsp;Chesnay]], France|publisher=[[National Institute for Research in Computer Science and Control|IRIA (now&nbsp;INRIA)]], Laboratoire de recherche en informatique et automatique|pages=41|}}. <!-- Ekeland cites this report in the ''[[Comptes Rendus|CRAS]]'' announcement of the results of his Appendix&nbsp;I -->
